---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "April 2026";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="License & Disclaimer — Tempo"
  description="Terms of use for Tempo: free to use, no warranty, you're responsible for what you automate.">
  <main class="legal">
    <p class="back"><a href="/">← tempoapp.app</a></p>

    <h1>License &amp; Disclaimer</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <p class="lede">
      Tempo is provided free of charge. You can use it for personal or
      commercial purposes. It comes with no warranty, and anything it does on
      your behalf — including anything you configure it to automate — is your
      responsibility.
    </p>

    <h2>License grant</h2>
    <p>
      You are granted a non-exclusive, non-transferable license to install and
      use Tempo on Macs you control, for any lawful purpose, at no cost. You
      may not redistribute, modify, reverse-engineer, or resell the Tempo
      application binary except as permitted by applicable law. You may freely
      write and share scores, configurations, and scripts that work with
      Tempo.
    </p>

    <h2>No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      Tempo is provided <strong>"as is"</strong>, without warranty of any
      kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the warranties of
      merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
      The author makes no guarantees that Tempo will be uninterrupted,
      error-free, or fit for your specific use case.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, the author shall not
      be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
      punitive damages, or any loss of data, revenue, profits, or business
      arising out of or in connection with your use of Tempo, even if advised
      of the possibility of such damages. Use Tempo at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2>Automation: you are the author</h2>
    <p>
      Tempo is built to execute automations — "scores" — that you author,
      install, or enable within the application. Tempo does not create,
      enable, or execute any score on your behalf. A fresh installation
      contains zero active automations.
    </p>
    <p>
      You are solely responsible for the scores you create, install, or run,
      and for the actions they perform, including but not limited to:
      opening URLs, running Terminal commands, invoking AppleScripts, posting
      to third-party services, modifying system state, or interacting with
      HomeKit accessories. Tempo maintains a local audit log of automatic
      actions so you can review what happened and when.
    </p>
    <p>
      Community-contributed scores — whether downloaded from the public Tempo
      Scores catalog or dropped into your local Scores folder from any other
      source — carry the same responsibility. The reviewed catalog includes a
      security and sanity check by the Tempo team, but that review is not a
      warranty. <strong>The functional responsibility of a score lies with
      its author, and the decision to install any score lies with you.</strong>
    </p>

    <h2>Network ingestion</h2>
    <p>
      Tempo's ingestion server accepts events from other hosts on your local
      network, protected by per-provider authentication tokens. You are
      responsible for the security of your local network, for the sources you
      authorize to send events, and for the secrets you configure. Tempo's
      role is to receive and display what you've authorized; it cannot audit
      the intent of the senders on your behalf.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party software</h2>
    <p>
      Tempo uses and bundles third-party open source components (SwiftUI,
      SQLite, Sparkle for updates, and others). These are used under their
      respective licenses. Full attribution is available in the application's
      <em>About → Acknowledgements</em> panel once shipped.
    </p>

    <h2>Trademarks</h2>
    <p>
      "Tempo" and the tempoapp.app domain are claimed by the project author.
      You may refer to Tempo by name in blog posts, reviews, screenshots, and
      other commentary. Do not use the name or visual identity to imply
      endorsement of unrelated products or services.
    </p>

    <h2>Freeware status and future changes</h2>
    <p>
      Tempo is distributed free of charge during the current release cycle.
      If a future major version introduces a paid tier, existing installs of
      free versions will remain usable at no cost. Any change to licensing or
      pricing will be announced on <a href="/">tempoapp.app</a> and in the
      application's release notes, with adequate notice.
    </p>

    <h2>Jurisdiction</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of Italy, without regard to
      conflict-of-law principles. If any provision is found unenforceable in
      your jurisdiction, the remaining provisions continue to apply.
    </p>
    <p>
      If you are a consumer resident in the European Union, the United Kingdom,
      or any other jurisdiction whose laws grant you mandatory consumer rights
      that cannot be waived by contract, those rights remain in force and are
      not affected by the choice of Italian law above. You may bring a claim
      in the competent court of the country where you reside.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:hello@tempoapp.app">hello@tempoapp.app</a>
    </p>
  </main>

  <style>
    .legal {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 48px auto;
      padding: 0 24px 80px;
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .legal .back {
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
    }
    .legal .back a {
      color: var(--blue);
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .legal h1 {
      font-size: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .legal h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
      margin-top: 40px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .legal .meta {
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--text2);
      margin-bottom: 32px;
    }
    .legal .lede {
      font-size: 17px;
      color: var(--text);
      padding: 16px 20px;
      background: var(--bg2);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
    }
    .legal ul { padding-left: 22px; }
    .legal li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .legal code {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.9em;
      background: var(--bg2);
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .legal a { color: var(--blue); }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
